From: Benoit Parrot <bparrot@ti.com>
Date: Fri, 5 Sep 2014 05:53:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1189/1587] media: ti-vpfe: driver restructuring to fix a
 kernel panic

While using 'yavta' the system team uncovered an issue with the way
the vpfe driver was handling it's mutex causing a deadlock.
Also as part of the upstream effort some of the review comment
suggested making uses of now available vb2 and v4l2 helper functions
to basically handle the locking mechanism.

Consequently the driver has been substancially cleaned up.
The exported/visible API have not changed.
This a cleaner more upstreamable version of vpfe capture driver.

